OL,3,CUS journalist Evan Gershkovich appears
OL,4,Cat closed-door trial in Russia
OL,6,FWith Mr Gerhkovich's trial being
OL,7,Fclosed, few details of his case may
OL,8,Fbecome public. But the Russian
OL,9,FProsecutor General's office said this
OL,10,Fmonth that he is accused of "gathering
OL,11,Fsecret information" on orders from the
OL,12,FCIA about Uralvagonzavod, a plant
OL,13,Fabout 150 kilometers (90 miles) north
OL,14,Fof Yekaterinburg that produces and
OL,15,Frepairs tanks and other military
OL,16,Fequipment.
OL,18,FRussia has not ruled out a prisoner
OL,19,Fexchange involving Mr Gershkovich but
OL,20,Fsays that's not possible before a
OL,21,Fverdict in his case.
